<item>
            <title>[LU-17263] &apos;lfs find -blocks&apos; should use 512-byte sectors by default</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17263</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lfs find -blocks&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; argument should be in 512-byte units by default to better match the bahevior of &quot;&lt;tt&gt;find(1)&lt;/tt&gt;&quot;, to make usage more portable between the two.  If a unit is specified, then this will still use the specified units.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For most cases this change will not be significant as users/scripts typically specify a suffix (e.g. &quot;&lt;tt&gt;-blocks 16M&lt;/tt&gt;&quot;), and this will be unaffected.  At worst, it will find files using 1/2 as much space as before.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
